{
  "texts": [
    "Another example of analyzing MD trajectories by performing classification task using the DL approach was performed in the context of G protein-coupled receptor (GPCR) structure and function.",
    "The main objective was to identify ligand-dependent conformational ensemble differences in GPCRs.",
    "Two receptor families were used, serotonin receptor subtype 2 A (5-HT2AR) and dopamine receptor subtype D2 (D2R), to which full, partial, or inverse agonists were bound.",
    "First, the MD trajectories were preprocessed to eliminate positional and orientational information.",
    "Then, the trajectories were transformed (frame by frame) into pixel representations that could be read by deep neural networks, where the values of red, green, and blue (RGB) corresponded to the x, y, and z coordinates of the atoms."
  ]
}